      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "peanut butter",
      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "mayonnaise",
      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "crushed almonds",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "optional, for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat until shimmering.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and sauté for 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Add the shrimp, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 2 minutes on each side until pink and opaque.",
    "Add the bell pepper, broccoli, zucchini, and onion, and stir‑fry for 5 minutes until vegetables are crisp‑tender.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, tomato paste, honey, peanut butter, and mayonnaise until smooth.",
    "Pour the sauce over the shrimp and vegetables and toss to coat; cook for an additional 2 minutes until the sauce thickens.",
    "Finish by drizzling the sesame oil over the dish and stirring in the crushed almonds for crunch.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with extra almonds if desired."
  ],
